title: Football Roundup: Crimson Streaks fall
text:
Football Roundup: Crimson Streaks fall 12:31 a.m. EDT October 4, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Edgerton 61, St. Joseph 14 
Andrew Guillaume ran for 196 yards and four touchdowns and Landon Thiel threw three touchdown passes and ran for another score Saturday as Edgerton (2-3) downed host St. Joseph (0-6). Chris Morrisette scored twice for the Crimson Streaks in the second period on runs of 47 and 68 yards and finished with 181 yards in 22 carries. 
The Bulldogs rolled up 408 total yards to 162 for St. Joseph, gaining 255 yards on the ground on 46 carries. Thiel hit 10 of 14 passes for 150 yards. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1Ro4A4p TOP VIDEOS
